Subject: Re: [VB] Help: excessively high oil pressure

The larger pump can supply more volume that may translate into some more
pressure. The only reason that you may actually need more volume is that the
engine has excessive clearances. The stock pump should be adequate unless
the engine is about to fail due to worn bearings anyway.

Chris
